<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>The Love Robot: From Sci-Fi Joke to Reality's Edge</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js"></script>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:wght@300;400;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
            background-color: #0a0a2a;
            color: #e0e0e0;
        }
        .section-card {
            background-color: rgba(20, 20, 50, 0.5);
            border: 1px solid rgba(100, 100, 220, 0.3);
            backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
            -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
            transition: all 0.5s ease-in-out;
            opacity: 0;
            transform: translateY(20px);
        }
        .section-card.is-visible {
            opacity: 1;
            transform: translateY(0);
        }
        .icon-glow {
            filter: drop-shadow(0 0 10px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.7));
        }
        .connector-line {
            width: 2px;
            height: 100%;
            background: linear-gradient(to bottom, transparent, #6d28d9, transparent);
            position: absolute;
            left: 50%;
            transform: translateX(-50%);
            z-index: -1;
        }
        .accent-text {
            color: #a78bfa;
        }
        .header-bg {
            background-image: url('https://images.pexels.com/photos/373543/pexels-photo-373543.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=1');
            background-size: cover;
            background-position: center;
            position: relative;
        }
        .header-bg::before {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
            right: 0;
            bottom: 0;
            background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(10, 10, 42, 0.7) 0%, #0a0a2a 85%);
        }
        .header-content {
            position: relative;
            z-index: 1;
        }
        .chart-container {
            max-height: 350px;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="overflow-x-hidden">

    <!-- Header Section -->
    <header class="text-center py-20 md:py-32 px-4 header-bg">
        <div class="header-content">
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-white mb-4">The Love Robot</h1>
            <p class="text-lg md:text-2xl text-violet-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">From a Sci-Fi Joke to Humanity's Next Great Question</p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Main Infographic Timeline -->
    <main class="relative py-12">
        <div class="connector-line"></div>
        <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
            <div class="space-y-24">

                <!-- 1. The Old Dream -->
                <section class="section-card rounded-2xl p-6 md:p-8 flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-8">
                    <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/7317730/pexels-photo-7317730.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=600" 
                         onerror="this.onerror=null;this.src='https://placehold.co/400x400/0a0a2a/e0e0e0?text=Vintage+Robot';"
                         alt="A classic tin toy robot" class="w-32 h-32 md:w-48 md:h-48 object-cover rounded-full flex-shrink-0 border-4 border-violet-500/50">
                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-3 text-white">The Past: A Silly Dream</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-300">The idea of a "love robot" was filed away with flying cars and jetpacksâ€”a charming but <span class="accent-text">cockamamie fantasy</span>. It was the punchline to a joke about technological overreach, born from lonely Saturday nights and sci-fi marathons.</p>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <!-- 2. The Paradigm Shift -->
                <section class="section-card rounded-2xl p-6 md:p-8">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-white text-center">The Shift: Building Blocks of a New Reality</h2>
                    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 mt-6">
                        <!-- The Mind -->
                        <div class="flex-1 text-center p-6 bg-black bg-opacity-20 rounded-xl">
                            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/8386440/pexels-photo-8386440.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=600"
                                 onerror="this.onerror=null;this.src='https://placehold.co/600x400/0a0a2a/e0e0e0?text=AI+Mind';"
                                 alt="Abstract visualization of an AI brain" class="rounded-lg w-full h-48 object-cover mb-4">
                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 text-white">The Mind: AI</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-300">Large Language Models ingested the sum of human expression. Not just chatbots, but a <span class="accent-text">mind without a body</span>, learning the patterns of our thoughts and language.</p>
                        </div>
                        <!-- The Body -->
                        <div class="flex-1 text-center p-6 bg-black bg-opacity-20 rounded-xl">
                             <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/8946343/pexels-photo-8946343.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=600"
                                  onerror="this.onerror=null;this.src='https://placehold.co/600x400/0a0a2a/e0e0e0?text=Robotic+Body';"
                                  alt="A humanoid robot under construction" class="rounded-lg w-full h-48 object-cover mb-4">
                            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 text-white">The Body: Robotics</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-300">Humanoids move with frightening grace. This isn't just pre-programmed mechanics; it's <span class="accent-text">synthetic biology</span>, teaching metal to interact with the world like a living thing.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <!-- 3. The Uncanny Valley -->
                <section class="section-card rounded-2xl p-6 md:p-8 flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-8">
                     <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/7391007/pexels-photo-7391007.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=600"
                          onerror="this.onerror=null;this.src='https://placehold.co/400x400/0a0a2a/e0e0e0?text=Uncanny+Valley';"
                          alt="A hyper-realistic android face" class="w-32 h-32 md:w-48 md:h-48 object-cover rounded-full flex-shrink-0 border-4 border-violet-500/50">
                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-3 text-white">The Present: Crossing the Uncanny Valley</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-300">We're building a bridge across the chasm of creepiness. With haptic feedback and advanced AI, the simulation of emotion could become so flawless that <span class="accent-text">our brains can no longer tell the difference</span>. The jerkiness is being replaced by fluency.</p>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <!-- 4. The Core Dilemma -->
                <section class="section-card rounded-2xl p-6 md:p-8">
                    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-center">
                        <div>
                            <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-3 text-white">The Dilemma: Where Does Connection Live?</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-300">If a machine can remember, joke, and converse, is its affection less valid? The great philosophical question is no longer academic: Does connection reside in the <span class="accent-text">neurons of the sender</span> or the <span class="accent-text">perception of the receiver</span>?</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="chart-container">
                             <canvas id="connectionPieChart"></canvas>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <!-- 5. Future Worry -->
                <section class="section-card rounded-2xl p-6 md:p-8">
                     <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-center">
                        <div>
                            <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-3 text-white">The Future: The Peril of Perfection</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-300">We're hurtling towards custom-order partners. What does this do to the messy project of human relationships? <span class="accent-text">Why learn to compromise</span> with a flawed human when you can have perfection delivered in a box?</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="chart-container">
                           <canvas id="partnerRadarChart"></canvas>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>
                
                <!-- 6. The Final Question -->
                <section class="section-card rounded-2xl p-6 md:p-8 text-center">
                    <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/7387349/pexels-photo-7387349.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=600"
                         onerror="this.onerror=null;this.src='https://placehold.co/600x300/0a0a2a/e0e0e0?text=Humanity's+Question';"
                         alt="A thoughtful female cyborg looking into the distance" class="w-full max-w-lg mx-auto h-64 object-cover rounded-xl mb-6 border-2 border-violet-500/50">
                    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">It's No Longer a Joke. It's a Question.</h2>
                    <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">Engineers and researchers are solving for dexterity and algorithms. That task falls to us. The love robot is a question aimed directly at the <span class="accent-text">heart of what it means to be human</span>. And the answer is coming soon.</p>
                </section>

            </div>
        </div>
    </main>

    <script>
        // JavaScript to add 'is-visible' class on scroll and render charts
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
            // Intersection Observer for animations
            const sections = document.querySelectorAll('.section-card');
            const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
                entries.forEach(entry => {
                    if (entry.isIntersecting) {
                        entry.target.classList.add('is-visible');
                    }
                });
            }, {
                threshold: 0.1
            });
            sections.forEach(section => {
                observer.observe(section);
            });

            // --- Chart.js Configuration ---
            
            // Common Chart Options
            Chart.defaults.color = '#e0e0e0';
            Chart.defaults.font.family = "'Poppins', sans-serif";

            // 1. Connection Pie Chart
            const pieCtx = document.getElementById('connectionPieChart');
            if (pieCtx) {
                new Chart(pieCtx, {
                    type: 'pie',
                    data: {
                        labels: ['Shared History', 'Emotional Resonance', 'Intellectual Stimulation', 'Physicality'],
                        datasets: [{
                            label: 'Components of Connection',
                            data: [20, 35, 30, 15],
                            backgroundColor: [
                                'rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.7)',
                                'rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.7)',
                                'rgba(109, 40, 217, 0.7)',
                                'rgba(91, 33, 182, 0.7)'
                            ],
                            borderColor: 'rgba(224, 224, 224, 0.5)',
                            borderWidth: 1
                        }]
                    },
                    options: {
                        responsive: true,
                        maintainAspectRatio: false,
                        plugins: {
                            legend: {
                                position: 'top',
                            },
                            title: {
                                display: true,
                                text: 'Perceived Components of Connection'
                            }
                        }
                    }
                });
            }

            // 2. Partner Attribute Radar Chart
            const radarCtx = document.getElementById('partnerRadarChart');
            if(radarCtx){
                new Chart(radarCtx, {
                    type: 'radar',
                    data: {
                        labels: ['Patience', 'Support', 'Shared Interests', 'Spontaneity', 'Growth', 'Compromise'],
                        datasets: [
                            {
                                label: 'AI Companion',
                                data: [10, 10, 10, 3, 5, 2],
                                fill: true,
                                backgroundColor: 'rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.2)',
                                borderColor: 'rgb(139, 92, 246)',
                                pointBackgroundColor: 'rgb(139, 92, 246)',
                                pointBorderColor: '#fff',
                                pointHoverBackgroundColor: '#fff',
                                pointHoverBorderColor: 'rgb(139, 92, 246)'
                            }, {
                                label: 'Human Partner',
                                data: [6, 7, 6, 8, 9, 8],
                                fill: true,
                                backgroundColor: 'rgba(54, 162, 235, 0.2)',
                                borderColor: 'rgb(54, 162, 235)',
                                pointBackgroundColor: 'rgb(54, 162, 235)',
                                pointBorderColor: '#fff',
                                pointHoverBackgroundColor: '#fff',
                                pointHoverBorderColor: 'rgb(54, 162, 235)'
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    options: {
                        responsive: true,
                        maintainAspectRatio: false,
                         scales: {
                            r: {
                                angleLines: { color: 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2)' },
                                grid: { color: 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2)' },
                                pointLabels: { font: { size: 12 } },
                                ticks: {
                                    backdropColor: 'transparent',
                                    stepSize: 2
                                }
                            }
                        },
                        plugins: {
                            title: {
                                display: true,
                                text: 'Partner Attribute Comparison'
                            }
                        }
                    }
                });
            }
        });
    </script>

</body>
</html>

